Sammy Jackson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sammy_Jackson 0 Sammy Jackson (August 18, 1937 – April 24, 1995) was an American actor, known particularly for his roles reflecting rural life, and a country music disc jockey, although he also played pop-standards during 1983 at Los Angeles's KMPC.
